  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-08-23",
    "date": "2022-01-14T13:27:37Z",
    "text": "Open Schools Responsibly Act\n\nThis bill limits civil liability for elementary and secondary schools and institutions of higher education relating to any harm arising from exposure to, or infection by, COVID-19 suffered by a student, employee, or visitor. Specifically, a school or institution shall not be liable for such harm if the school or institution was in compliance with applicable state requirements. However, a school or institution may be liable for acts or omissions that constitute willful or criminal misconduct, gross negligence, reckless misconduct, or a conscious flagrant indifference to the rights or safety of the individual harmed."
  },
